      "side": 1,
      "message": "Opening a not-recorded span simplifies the code (no need to do \u0027if span !\u003d nil\u0027 checks in a bunch of places) and also makes sure if some of health check code accidentally (or not) opens a span, this span will be ignored (since it will be a child of not-recorded span). Added comment.",
